%N A392925 Smallest odd number k greater than 1 such that sigma_n(k)/k is an integer.
%C A392925 a(1) corresponds to odd multiperfect numbers greater than 1, if they exist.
%C A392925 Does every integer greater than 1 have a solution?
%C A392925 65 is a solution for every positive n congruent to 2 mod 4.
%H A392925 Alexander Violette, <a href="/A392925/b392925.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..200</a>
%H A392925 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divisor_function">Divisor function</a>
%e A392925 65 is the smallest odd number k > 1 such that sigma_2(k)/k is an integer, hence a(2)=65.
%o A392925 (PARI) a(n) = my(k=3); while (sigma(k,n) % k, k+=2); k; \\ _Michel Marcus_, May 30 2026
